<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Cyclist Breaks World Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- France's Arnaud Tournant broke the world
record in the men's kilometer sprint Friday during the World Cup
track event, the government news agency Notimex reported.
</P>
<P>
   Tournant finished in 1 minute, 0.148 seconds to break the mark
of 1:00.60 set by Australia's Shane Kelly in the 1995 world
championships in Colombia.
</P>
<P>
   ''For months now we had been trying to reach the world record in
a race against the clock, which fortunately we did today,'' said
Gerard Quimtyn, Tounant's coach.
</P>
<P>
   Ben Kersten of Australia was second in 1:02.84.
</P>
</TEXT>
