<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Prep School Gays Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EXETER, N.H. (AP) -- In a June 16 story about Phillips Exeter
Academy allowing gay and lesbian faculty and staff to serve as
dormitory parents, The Associated Press quoted a teen-ager who said
he was a student at the school and gave his name as Scott Taylor.
</P>
<P>
   School officials say no one by that name is enrolled at the
school.
</P>
