<HEADLINE> UCLA Linebacker Arrested  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- UCLA football player Asi Faoa was arrested
Friday at his dormitory on a felony charge of mayhem, stemming from
brain injuries sustained by another student during a party.
</P>
<P>
   Faoa, 19, was held in lieu of $100,000 bail pending his
arraignment, scheduled for Monday.
</P>
<P>
   During an April 30 block party near the campus, Faoa and Rodrigo
Dezubriria were dancing when Faoa's elbow struck the other
student's head, said Officer Eduardo Funes, a police spokesman. A
criminal complaint alleged that Dezubriria sustained severe brain
damage.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-4, 240-pound Faoa was a redshirt freshman linebacker
for the Bruins last year and did not play.
</P>
<P>
   He has been indefinitely suspended from the team because of the
charge, UCLA athletic director Peter Dalis said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We will investigate the situation before making any other
decision,'' Dalis said.
</P>
</TEXT>
