<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sam Jackson Gets Walk of Fame Star  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Wearing all black and his signature Kangol
hat, Samuel L. Jackson was clearly the coolest cat on Hollywood
Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
   About 500 fans gathered curbside Friday to watch the ''Shaft''
star unveil his sidewalk star, the 2,195th dedicated along the
famous Hollywood Walk of Fame.
</P>
<P>
   ''Who woulda thunk it?'' Jackson asked. ''I remember coming here
in 1969 and looking at all the names on the boulevard. It never
came across my mind that I would be a part of this ever -- even if I
was in the business.''
</P>
<P>
   Jackson, 51, was surrounded by family members who also were in
town for his daughter's high school graduation. Friends at the
ceremony included William Friedkin, who directed Jackson in ''Rules
of Engagement,'' and Dustin Hoffman.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson's other movie credits include ''Pulp Fiction,'' ''A Time
to Kill'' and ''Star Wars: Episode One -- The Phantom Menace.''
''Shaft'' opened nationwide Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
