<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-17 02:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sir Michael Caine Likes New Title  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- British actor Michael Caine said he was ecstatic
with the new title bestowed upon him by Queen Elizabeth II.
</P>
<P>
   Just call him, Sir Michael.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's the greatest day of my life,'' Caine said Friday, after
the queen conferred the title of knight upon him.
</P>
<P>
   The queen's Birthday Honors List is selected by the Labor Party
government to honor people in all walks of life for their
contributions to their professions and to charity.
</P>
<P>
   The honors include, in descending order, knighthood and its
female equivalent, dame; the Commander of the Order of the British
Empire, or CBE; Member of the Order of British Empire, MBE; and
Officer of the Order of the British Empire, OBE.
</P>
<P>
   Others receiving knighthood were Paddy Ashdown, former leader of
the Liberal Democrats, Eddie George, governor of the Bank of
England and men's clothing designer Paul Smith.
</P>
<P>
   The honor of dame was bestowed upon novelist Beryl Bainbridge
and opera singer Anne Evans.
</P>
<P>
   Those who received the honor of CBE included Tina Brown, the
British-born editor of Talk magazine, mystery writer Dick Francis
and Sam Mendes, director of the Oscar-winning movie ''American
Beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   Pete King, proprietor of famous London jazz club Ronnie Scott's,
was among those honored as MBE. J.K. Rowling, author of the
best-selling Harry Potter books, and mystery writer Colin Dexter
were among those receiving OBE honors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
