<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trenton man sentenced to life for strip club killing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   DOYLESTOWN, Pa. (AP) - A Bucks County jury sentenced a New
Jersey man convicted of killing a gambling buddy at a Bristol
Township strip club to life in prison.
</P>
<P>
   After seven hours of jury deliberations, DeWayne Housley was
found guilty Thursday of first-degree murder in the February 1999
killing of Charles Bethea, 53, of Yardville, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Housley, 24, of Trenton, N.J., was automatically sentenced to
life in prison after jurors met Friday for a death penalty hearing
and were unable to reach a decision.
</P>
<P>
   Bethea, an employee at the New Jersey Department of Labor, was
waiting outside Divas International Gentleman's Club for his
girlfriend, an exotic dancer who had been called by the club to
fill in for the evening.
</P>
<P>
   Police said codefendent Courtney Page Boone, 21, of Trenton,
N.J., and Housley knew Bethea from hanging out in illegal gambling
halls. They believed that Bethea carried a lot of cash and planned
to rob him.
</P>
<P>
   Housley and Bethea fought, police said, and Bethea was chased
into the club. Just inside the door, police said, Housley shot
Bethea in the face, then fled.
</P>
<P>
   Boone, who claimed he stayed in the car during the killing,
pleaded guilty in April to third-degree murder and agreed to
testify against Housley.
</P>
</TEXT>
