<HEADLINE> Same three digits picked two nights in a row in New York Numbers drawing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - Lottery players - and state officials who
pick the numbers - did a doubletake Friday when the same three New
York Numbers popped up in the same order for the second day in a
row.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a completely random occurrence,'' said Susan Miller,
Lottery spokeswoman. ''Different machines, different balls.''
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday and Friday, the numbers selected were 0, 8, and 4.
The top prize for the game is $500.
</P>
<P>
   Miller could not say what the odds were of the numbers coming up
twice in random drawings.
</P>
<P>
   The Win 4 numbers were also similar on both nights, though in
different orders. On Thursday, 0, 8, 7, 1 popped up and on Friday
the Win 4 numbers were 8, 9, 1, and 0.
</P>
</TEXT>
