<HEADLINE> Germany Opens Wind-Power Plant  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BERLIN (AP) -- Europe's biggest wind-power plant was inaugurated
Saturday outside Berlin, bolstering Germany's claim as a leader in
the use of renewable energy.
</P>
<P>
   The plant's windmills will feed power into the regional
electricity network from the town of Klettwitz, about 75 miles
south of Berlin, officials said. The 38 windmills will provide
electricity for 30,000 households.
</P>
<P>
   Germany has about 8,000 windmills that generate power. The
government recently embarked on a major program to promote solar
and wind power.
</P>
