<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ontario Students' Bodies Found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOBERMORY, Canada (AP) -- Rescuers on Saturday pulled the bodies
of two 12-year-old students from Lake Huron's Georgian Bay, where
they had disappeared after the glass-bottomed boat they were on
sank.
</P>
<P>
   The two Ontario students -- Henricki Foerster and Wade Simmons --
were on a school tour Friday when the 33-foot True North II went
down near Flowerpot Island, a popular tourist destination on the
lake.
</P>
<P>
   A Canadian Coast Guard vessel rescued 15 students, two teachers
and the boat's captain on Friday. But the boy and girl were still
missing when the search was suspended overnight.
</P>
<P>
   After a six-hour search Saturday, divers found the pair several
hundred yards from the sunken vessel.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities were still investigating what caused the boat to
sink during the outing for seventh graders from Tiverton, Ontario.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
