<HEADLINE> Teen critical after incident at Buena Vista lake  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BUENA VISTA, N.J. (AP) - A teen-ager was in critical condition
Saturday after nearly drowning at a campground lake, state police
said.
</P>
<P>
   The 14-year-old girl was swimming in the lake at Buena Vista
Campground at about 2:45 p.m. when other swimmers saw that she had
gone under the water, said Trooper Dean Carnival.
</P>
<P>
   Lifeguards pulled her from the water and performed
cardiopulmonary resuscitation. The girl, whose name and hometown
were not released, was flown to Cooper Hospital-University Medical
Center in Camden, where she was in critical but stable condition.
</P>
