<HEADLINE> 73-year-old motorcyclist dies after fall into river  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) - A 73-year-old motorcyclist who flipped over
a bridge and fell 60 feet to the Susquehanna River died early
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Kimball Carroll of Endicott was riding his 1983 Suzuki
motorcycle to a routine inspection Friday afternoon when he hit the
curb and flipped over the side, leaving the motorcycle on the
bridge, investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   He was pulled out of the river about 15 minutes later at a park
about a mile downstream. He was pronounced dead at 1:30 a.m. at a
regional hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred about 3:45 p.m. in the eastbound lane of
The River Bridge carrying Route 17 between Vestal and Endwell.
</P>
