<HEADLINE> Sol 55, Rockers 48  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Sheri Sam scored a season-high 21 points as the
Miami Sol withstood a late rally to beat the Cleveland Rockers
55-48 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Marlies Askamp added 10 points for Miami, which won its second
straight home game.
</P>
<P>
   Chasity Melvin scored 11 points and had seven rebounds, and
Suzie McConnell Serio added 10 points for the Rockers.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (3-5) led 51-39 with 6:42 to play before the Rockers (5-3)
went on a 9-0 run to pull within three. But Cleveland failed to
score the final 4:12 of the game.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol weren't much better, going 6:30 without scoring during a
late stretch before Katrina Colleton converted a pair of free
throws and Sam scored on a layup in the final seconds.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol, who led 30-26 at the half, pushed the lead to 45-35
with 12:02 to play on a 3-pointer from the right side by Sam, but
couldn't put it away.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams were plagued by turnovers, as they each committed 19.
</P>
<P>
   Miami was coming off an embarrassing 77-53 loss to the
three-time WNBA champion Houston Comets on Thursday in which it
tied a league record for fewest first-half points (13).
</P>
<P>
   The Sol, which shot only 19 percent in the first half against
Houston, did much better Saturday shooting 44.4 percent. Miami
jumped out to an 8-2 lead as Debbie Black and Sam made 3-point
jumpers on consecutive possessions.
</P>
<P>
   After tying it at 20, the Rockers, coming off a loss to Indiana
that snapped a five-game winning streak, took their first lead --
22-20 with 5:38 left -- on an 18-footer by Vicki Hall.
</P>
<P>
   Miami shot 54.5 percent from beyond the 3-point arc, including
4-of-7 by Sam.
</P>
</TEXT>
