<HEADLINE> Fever 79, Miracle 54  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Alicia Thompson scored 17 points and Rita
Williams added 16 as the Indiana Fever beat the Orlando Miracle
79-54 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana reserve Gordana Grubin scored 13 points, and Danielle
McCulley added 12 as the Fever used lopsided runs at the end of
each half to snap a three-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Taj McWilliams led Orlando with 11 points, and Shannon Johnson
scored 10 as the only Miracle players in double figures.
</P>
<P>
   The Fever finished the game on a 20-4 run after outscoring
Orlando 25-8 to close out the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando trimmed Indiana's lead to 59-50 on a basket by Nykesha
Sales at 7:22 of the second half, as the Fever struggled by only
making six of their first 23 shots of the half.
</P>
<P>
   But Orlando could not get any closer as Indiana held the Miracle
to only four points following Sales' basket. Orlando had four
turnovers and a technical foul called on coach Carolyn Peck in the
final 6:32.
</P>
<P>
   The game was tied 23-23 with 7:53 remaining in the first half
when Indiana pulled away to take 48-31 lead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana shot 8-for-19 from 3-point range, while Orlando was
1-of-16.
</P>
</TEXT>
