<HEADLINE> NL Umpire Greg Bonin Injured  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Umpire Greg Bonin was removed from the field
by ambulance after he was knocked down by a foul ball off his mask
in the eighth inning of Saturday night's game between Florida and
Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   Bonin was working behind the plate when Pittsburgh's Wil Cordero
fouled a pitch from Braden Looper straight back. It struck Bonin
with enough force to knock off his mask and immediately force him
to the ground.
</P>
<P>
   Bonin remained stretched out in the dirt around home plate as
trainers from both teams and Pirates doctors attended. With the
assistance of paramedics, they applied a brace to immobilize his
neck.
</P>
<P>
   Bonin was moving his legs before he was strapped to a stretcher.
An ambulance then drove onto the field to take him to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Bonin, who turned 45 on Thursday, became a regular member of the
NL umpiring staff in April 1986.
</P>
<P>
   After a 16-minute delay, the game continued with three umpires.
</P>
</TEXT>
