<HEADLINE> Escaped bees cause buzz at Thruway rest stop  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CHITTENANGO, N.Y. (AP) - Thousands of bees escaped from a truck
at the Chittenango rest stop on the state Thruway Friday, stinging
several people and closing down three diesel fuel pumps.
</P>
<P>
   Just before 4 p.m. a gas station attendant noticed the bees
swarming in the air. A truck carrying bees was pulling away, but
the attendant could not get the driver to stop, police said. They
were unable to find the driver.
</P>
<P>
   The bees stung one man six times in the face and twice in the
arm. He did not require medical attention.
</P>
<P>
   The bees swarmed around the fuel pumps and a pickup parked
nearby, keeping truckers and their gas-starved rigs at bay.
Hundreds of them clumped to the underside of the red pumps and to
the driver's side window of the pickup.
</P>
<P>
   A trapper lured most of the bees into a box and his car using
honey and pheromones.
</P>
<P>
   Several truck drivers waited four hours at the rest stop,
between exits 34 and 34A of the state's main highway.
</P>
<P>
   Chittenango is 14 miles east of Syracuse.
</P>
</TEXT>
