<HEADLINE> Fire 3, United 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Fire scored all of their goals in a
15-minute span in the second half to beat D.C. United 3-2 Saturday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Josh Wolff opened the scoring by getting the ball past United
goalie Tom Presthus in the 67th minute, starting a spurt in which
four goals were scored in nine minutes.
</P>
<P>
   With back-to-back goals in the 70th and 74th minutes, the United
took a 2-1 lead. But the Fire's Diego Gutierrez tied it just two
minutes later off a pass from Peter Nowak.
</P>
<P>
   Nowak scored in the 82nd minute off passes from Wolff and Jesse
Marschm to win it.
</P>
<P>
   Presthus had five saves, while Chicago goalkeeper Zach Thornton
had two.
</P>
