<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-17 23:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Galaxy 2, Mutiny 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Simon Elliott and Danny Califf scored
first-half goals as the Los Angeles Galaxy ended a four-game
winless streak by beating the Tampa Bay Mutiny 2-1 Saturday night
in Major League Soccer.
</P>
<P>
   Manny Lagos scored during injury time in the second half for
Tampa Bay (8-7), taking Carlos Valderrama's pass and putting a shot
under goalkeeper Kevin Hartman for his fifth goal.
</P>
<P>
   Before 14,603 at the Rose Bowl, Valderrama missed a penalty kick
in the 47th minute, putting it against the left post.
</P>
<P>
   Elliott opened the scoring in the ninth minute after referee
Noel Kenny awarded the Galaxy the free kick for Eric Quill's foul
of Luis Hernandez 25 yards from the goal.
</P>
<P>
   Mauricio Cienfuegos and Greg Vanney both made runs at the ball,
but Elliott eventually took the kick, putting it over goalkeeper
Scott Garlick's right arm for his third goal of the season.
</P>
<P>
   A rookie defender, Califf got inside of defender Ritchie
Kotschau to head Vanney's corner kick in from six yards out in the
40th minute for his first MLS goal.
</P>
<P>
   Kenny awarded Tampa Bay the penalty kick following a collision
between Vanney and Manny Lagos on the left side of the penalty
area.
</P>
</TEXT>
